### Safety Score & Analytics API Examples
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or any HTTP client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api/safety-score

###############################################################################
# 1. Calculate Safety Score for a Location
###############################################################################

### Example 1.1: Calculate score for Indiranagar
GET {{baseUrl}}/calculate?lat=12.9716&lng=77.5946&radius=1000

### Example 1.2: Calculate score for Koramangala (High Crime Area)
GET {{baseUrl}}/calculate?lat=12.9352&lng=77.6245&radius=1000

### Example 1.3: Calculate score for Basavanagudi (Low Crime Area)
GET {{baseUrl}}/calculate?lat=12.9423&lng=77.5742&radius=1000

### Example 1.4: Calculate score with larger radius (2km)
GET {{baseUrl}}/calculate?lat=12.9716&lng=77.5946&radius=2000

###############################################################################
# 2. Simulate Infrastructure Improvements
###############################################################################

### Example 2.1: Add 5 streetlights to Koramangala
POST {{baseUrl}}/simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lat": 12.9352,
  "lng": 77.6245,
  "radius": 1000,
  "changes": {
    "addStreetlights": 5,
    "addPoliceBooths": 0,
    "fixIssues": 0
  }
}

### Example 2.2: Add 2 police booths to Whitefield
POST {{baseUrl}}/simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lat": 12.9698,
  "lng": 77.7499,
  "radius": 1000,
  "changes": {
    "addStreetlights": 0,
    "addPoliceBooths": 2,
    "fixIssues": 0
  }
}

### Example 2.3: Comprehensive improvement (lights + booths + fix issues)
POST {{baseUrl}}/simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lat": 12.9352,
  "lng": 77.6245,
  "radius": 1000,
  "changes": {
    "addStreetlights": 5,
    "addPoliceBooths": 2,
    "fixIssues": 3
  }
}

### Example 2.4: Fix broken streetlights in BTM Layout
POST {{baseUrl}}/simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lat": 12.9165,
  "lng": 77.6101,
  "radius": 1000,
  "changes": {
    "addStreetlights": 0,
    "addPoliceBooths": 0,
    "fixIssues": 5
  }
}

###############################################################################
# 3. Get All Area Scores
###############################################################################

### Example 3.1: Get safety scores for all Bengaluru areas
GET {{baseUrl}}/areas

###############################################################################
# 4. Get Crime Data
###############################################################################

### Example 4.1: Get crime rate data for all areas
GET {{baseUrl}}/crime-data

###############################################################################
# 5. Generate Safety Heatmap
###############################################################################

### Example 5.1: Generate heatmap for Bengaluru center (8x8 grid)
GET {{baseUrl}}/heatmap?center_lat=12.9716&center_lng=77.5946&grid_size=8

### Example 5.2: Generate heatmap for Koramangala area (10x10 grid)
GET {{baseUrl}}/heatmap?center_lat=12.9352&center_lng=77.6245&grid_size=10

### Example 5.3: Generate smaller heatmap (5x5 grid) for faster response
GET {{baseUrl}}/heatmap?center_lat=12.9716&center_lng=77.5946&grid_size=5

###############################################################################
# 6. Get Safety Score Trends
###############################################################################

### Example 6.1: Get 30-day trend for Indiranagar
GET {{baseUrl}}/trends?lat=12.9716&lng=77.5946&days=30

### Example 6.2: Get 7-day trend for Koramangala
GET {{baseUrl}}/trends?lat=12.9352&lng=77.6245&days=7

### Example 6.3: Get 90-day trend for Basavanagudi
GET {{baseUrl}}/trends?lat=12.9423&lng=77.5742&days=90

###############################################################################
# 7. Compare Multiple Locations
###############################################################################

### Example 7.1: Compare high crime vs low crime areas
POST {{baseUrl}}/compare
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "locations": [
    {
      "name": "Koramangala (High Crime)",
      "lat": 12.9352,
      "lng": 77.6245
    },
    {
      "name": "Basavanagudi (Low Crime)",
      "lat": 12.9423,
      "lng": 77.5742
    }
  ]
}

### Example 7.2: Compare three major tech hubs
POST {{baseUrl}}/compare
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "locations": [
    {
      "name": "Koramangala",
      "lat": 12.9352,
      "lng": 77.6245
    },
    {
      "name": "Indiranagar",
      "lat": 12.9716,
      "lng": 77.5946
    },
    {
      "name": "Whitefield",
      "lat": 12.9698,
      "lng": 77.7499
    }
  ]
}

### Example 7.3: Compare all South Bengaluru areas
POST {{baseUrl}}/compare
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "locations": [
    {
      "name": "Koramangala",
      "lat": 12.9352,
      "lng": 77.6245,
      "radius": 1000
    },
    {
      "name": "Jayanagar",
      "lat": 12.9250,
      "lng": 77.5838,
      "radius": 1000
    },
    {
      "name": "BTM Layout",
      "lat": 12.9165,
      "lng": 77.6101,
      "radius": 1000
    },
    {
      "name": "JP Nagar",
      "lat": 12.9081,
      "lng": 77.5855,
      "radius": 1000
    },
    {
      "name": "Basavanagudi",
      "lat": 12.9423,
      "lng": 77.5742,
      "radius": 1000
    }
  ]
}

###############################################################################
# 8. Real-World Scenarios
###############################################################################

### Scenario 1: Urban Planner - Find areas needing most improvement
# Step 1: Get all area scores
GET {{baseUrl}}/areas

# Step 2: Calculate detailed score for worst area (Koramangala)
GET {{baseUrl}}/calculate?lat=12.9352&lng=77.6245&radius=1000

# Step 3: Simulate improvements
POST {{baseUrl}}/simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lat": 12.9352,
  "lng": 77.6245,
  "radius": 1000,
  "changes": {
    "addStreetlights": 10,
    "addPoliceBooths": 3,
    "fixIssues": 5
  }
}

###

### Scenario 2: Budget Allocation - Compare ROI of different investments
# Option A: Add 10 streetlights
POST {{baseUrl}}/simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lat": 12.9352,
  "lng": 77.6245,
  "radius": 1000,
  "changes": {
    "addStreetlights": 10,
    "addPoliceBooths": 0,
    "fixIssues": 0
  }
}

###

# Option B: Add 5 police booths
POST {{baseUrl}}/simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lat": 12.9352,
  "lng": 77.6245,
  "radius": 1000,
  "changes": {
    "addStreetlights": 0,
    "addPoliceBooths": 5,
    "fixIssues": 0
  }
}

###

# Option C: Balanced approach
POST {{baseUrl}}/simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lat": 12.9352,
  "lng": 77.6245,
  "radius": 1000,
  "changes": {
    "addStreetlights": 5,
    "addPoliceBooths": 2,
    "fixIssues": 3
  }
}

###

### Scenario 3: Citizen Safety - Find safest route between two points
# Compare safety scores of intermediate areas
POST {{baseUrl}}/compare
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "locations": [
    {
      "name": "Route A: Via Koramangala",
      "lat": 12.9352,
      "lng": 77.6245
    },
    {
      "name": "Route B: Via Jayanagar",
      "lat": 12.9250,
      "lng": 77.5838
    },
    {
      "name": "Route C: Via Basavanagudi",
      "lat": 12.9423,
      "lng": 77.5742
    }
  ]
}

###

### Scenario 4: Performance Tracking - Monitor improvements over time
# Get current score
GET {{baseUrl}}/calculate?lat=12.9352&lng=77.6245&radius=1000

###

# Get historical trend
GET {{baseUrl}}/trends?lat=12.9352&lng=77.6245&days=90

###

# Compare with neighboring areas
POST {{baseUrl}}/compare
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "locations": [
    {
      "name": "Koramangala",
      "lat": 12.9352,
      "lng": 77.6245
    },
    {
      "name": "BTM Layout (Neighbor)",
      "lat": 12.9165,
      "lng": 77.6101
    },
    {
      "name": "Jayanagar (Neighbor)",
      "lat": 12.9250,
      "lng": 77.5838
    }
  ]
}

###############################################################################
# 9. Edge Cases and Testing
###############################################################################

### Test 9.1: Invalid coordinates (should return error)
GET {{baseUrl}}/calculate?lat=invalid&lng=77.5946&radius=1000

###

### Test 9.2: Missing parameters (should return error)
GET {{baseUrl}}/calculate?lat=12.9716

###

### Test 9.3: Very large radius (should still work)
GET {{baseUrl}}/calculate?lat=12.9716&lng=77.5946&radius=10000

###

### Test 9.4: Zero changes simulation (should return same score)
POST {{baseUrl}}/simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lat": 12.9352,
  "lng": 77.6245,
  "radius": 1000,
  "changes": {
    "addStreetlights": 0,
    "addPoliceBooths": 0,
    "fixIssues": 0
  }
}

###

### Test 9.5: Extreme changes (should cap at reasonable values)
POST {{baseUrl}}/simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lat": 12.9352,
  "lng": 77.6245,
  "radius": 1000,
  "changes": {
    "addStreetlights": 100,
    "addPoliceBooths": 50,
    "fixIssues": 100
  }
}

###############################################################################
# Notes:
# - All coordinates are for Bengaluru, India
# - Radius is in meters (default: 1000m = 1km)
# - Scores range from 0-100
# - Grades: A+ (90-100), A (80-89), B (70-79), C (60-69), D (50-59), F (0-49)
# - Crime rates are per 1000 people per year
###############################################################################
